snippet.textDisplay: The concept of sailing for months to a distant land and setting up in the wilderness, surrounded by hostile tribes, then watching your only method of escape sail away, knowing that at best it'll be a long time before it can return, and it could very well NEVER return, stranding you there for the rest of your life, is absolutely terrifying. And you wouldn't even have a method of communicating with anyone. You couldn't send a message saying "When are you returning?". These colonists were made of far tougher stuff than I am; I could never even consider doing this.
